additional_info:
11/13/2015: restored right sidebar with most recent global threads on forum pages

You have the option to hide some elements in the UserExtraInfo box, which is at the top-right of each post. Currently you can hide Political Party, Likes count, marital status and the Blessings Count. You can also hide the user avatar over each post .

With CF open in a tab, click on the Stylish toolbar icon and under this style select "edit". In the Code box go to the bottom and you will see the "Hide User Extra Info Elements" section. Now Unquote the elements you want to hide. This is done by simply removing the /* and */ that encompass each element in the code. For instance:

/*Hide Politics*/
/* div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl.pairsJustified.userField_political_party.xbCustomField {display:none } */

would become:

/*Hide Politics*/
div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl.pairsJustified.userField_political_party.xbCustomField {display:none }

css:
@-moz-document domain("christianforums.com") {
/*  ALL */
div.xbBoxed { background-color:gray }
/*  OPTIONAL -kill red media number in navbar
li.navTab.xengallery.Popup.PopupControl.PopupClosed.PopupContainerControl a.navLink strong.itemCount { visibility:hidden }  */

/* ALL FORUMS PAGE */
ol#forums.nodeList.sectionMain { background-color:gray  }
div.secondaryContent { background-color:lightgray  }

/* FORUM (THREAD LIST) */
/*div.mainContainer { background-color:gray }*/

li.discussionListItem.visible.locked.sticky, li.discussionListItem.visible.visible.sticky, div.sectionFooter { background-color:lightgray }

div.xbStickyBar { background-color:gray }
li.discussionListItem.visible { background-color:#cbe3d6 }

li.nodelist.forum.level_2,  form.sectionMain ol.nodeList  { background-color: lightgray !important }

/* THREAD */
div.thread_view { width: 800px  }
div.messageHeading { height: 10px }
div.messageUserInfo, div.messageUserBlock { background-color:gray !important }
div.extraUserInfo { background-color:lightgray !important }
a.username span.style8 { color:black !important }

div.messageContent, div.messageInfo.primaryContent, blockquote.messageText, div.pageContent { 
    background-color:#ece8cd !important; 
    font-size:14px !important; 
    font-family:"deja vu sans", verdana 
    }
div.quote { background-color:lightgray }

/* EDITOR */
/* body tag is for full editor; doesn't hit main pages */
div.quickReply.message, body, body[contenteditable="true"]  { background-color:#e1e3e2; } 
body > p, body > indent, blockquote { font-family:"deja vu sans", verdana; font-size:14px } 

/* HIDE USER EXTRA INFO ELEMENTS */
/* Remove the quote marks that surround each element you want to hide */

/*Hide Politics*/
div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl.pairsJustified.userField_political_party.xbCustomField {display:none }

/* Hide blessings count */
 xbCustomField,  div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl:nth-child(4) {display:none }

/*Hide Married status*/
div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl.pairsJustified.userField_marital_status.xbCustomField {display:none }

/* Hide Likes count */
div.messageUserInfo > div > div.extraUserInfo > dl.pairsJustified.xbLikes {display:none }  

/* Hide Avatar in threads */
/* div.avatarHolder { display:none }*/

/* NW Hide Likes count in own User box */
/*div.pairsJustified dt[Likes]{text: }*/
}

@-moz-document url("http://www.christianforums.com/watched/forums") {
li.node.forum.level-n.node_800, h4.nodeTitle a { color: gray !important}
}
